    <name>
      <text>8.2.22 (Find sum of GP (with surds))</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>What is the sum of the first {@n@} terms of the geometric progression \({@aval@}+{@aval@}\sqrt{{@k@}}+{@ev(aval*k,simp)@}+{@ev(aval*k,simp)@}\sqrt{@k@}+\cdots\)?</p><p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>The partial sum \(S_{n}\) of the first \(n\) terms of a geometric progression, first term \(a\) and common ratio \(r\), is given by the equation \[ S_{n}=\frac{a(1-r^n)}{1 - r}. \] Here \(a = {@aval@}\) and \(r = {@rval@}\) so \(S_{@n@} = {@sum1@}\).</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
